[]  1) Large BUFFER_SIZE (>1024)
[]  2) Small BUFFER_SIZE (< 8, and 1)
[]  3) BUFFER_SIZE exactly the length of the line to read
[]  4) 1 byte variant (+/-) between the line and the BUFFER_SIZE
[]  5) Read on stdin
[]  6) Read from a file
[]  7) (Multiple/Single) Long line (2k+ characters) 
[]  8) (Multiple/Single) Short line (< 4 characters, even 1)
[]  9) (Multiple/Single) Empty line


FROM A FILE and FROM STDIN
[]  1 with 3, 4, 7, 8 and 9 
[]  2 with 3, 4, 7, 8 and 9 
